What indicates that Russia is getting out of the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest in the last twenty years of the recession.
According to analysts polled by Bloomberg, the GDP of the Russian Federation is showing a positive dynamic - in the second quarter GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This figure has been minimal since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data from Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development have also recently announced the stabilization of the situation.
Forward is slow growth.
According to experts of the Central Bank, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
“The index estimate of Russian GDP shows that the recession is behind and ahead of the slow growth of the economy,” says the Bank of Russia’s bulletin “What the trends are saying.”
The modular estimate of GDP in the current quarter of the regulator has increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter the decline of GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally-cleaned decline in GDP was 0.2% to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter, the decline stopped: in April it was 0.2%, and in May and June the change in GDP was within 0-0.15”, – RIA Novosti MERCEDES-MER representative.
The slowdown in the decline of the Russian economy over the last five quarters indicates that the “bottom has passed”.
Among other markers pointing to signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the rise in demand for electricity and rail transport, a revival of business.
If you make a correction to the fact that the year is high, it is clear that the dynamics plus 1% of electricity consumption can be due in half to the additional working day.
Let’s add to this a lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight transport, but it is difficult to get accurate data here, and a plus-minus of 0.5% of half-year volume can also be explained by seasonality,” explains Kirill Yakovenko of ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, a reduction in price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2%, compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, the last two weeks Rosstat has fixed deflation.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble rate, which, although showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, according to the results of August since the beginning of the year has strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy”, - emphasizes Yakovenko.
In addition, since April, there has been an increase in the volume of industrial production in the Russian Federation.
In June, the figure grew by 1.7%.
The rate of foreign trade declines from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
The positive dynamics is also demonstrated by the situation in the labour market, where the unemployment rate has decreased to 5.4%.
Below it was only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the well-being of the labour market, the question of the real disposable income of the population is left to want the best.
In annual terms, the figure is reduced by 4.8%.
This factor can hamper the recovery of the economy, as household expenditures make a significant contribution to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy, their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, as risk factors for economic growth can also be called the strict policy of the Bank of Russia.
The regulator holds the rate at 10.5%, which does not have the best impact on the real sector.
A negative factor is and is not a sufficiently high level of investment, which inhibits the development of industrial capacity.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year, the rate of decline of the Russian economy will slow to -0.5% versus -3.7% in 2015," says Irina Rogova, an analyst at the Forex Club.
