In particular, as the Mufti pointed out, this was practiced in the Burnaev Mosque, Zakaban and Eniler.
However, Mr. Mukhametshin stressed, the leadership sets the task of having all students possess both state languages of the republic, regardless of nationality.
"There can be no mention of any insult to the Muslim-Netatar," said Mr. Mukhamethin, explaining that the sermon itself "is not a mandatory, major part of the prayer."
At the same time, the prayer itself will continue to be read in Arabic, lectures and lessons in Russian will be held in the mosques.
At the same time, Rafik Muhametshin said "E" that there was no serious threat of expulsion of the Tatar language from mosques.
Apart from Russian and Tatar, other languages, for example, Uzbek or Tajik, according to him, are not used in the sermons in the republic.
The DUM decision was actively supported by the Executive Committee of the World Tatar Congress (WCC).
