The Russian copper company (RMK) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that the RMK has taken on the modernization of one of the oldest and ecologically "dirty" enterprises in the country - the Karabash medelavyna.
The Karabash Medellin Plant was founded by an English joint stock company led by Leslie Urquart in 1910.
In Soviet times it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country's economy, and it actually provided the vitality of the entire city.
However, in the 1990s, due to financial problems, production was halted, resulting in serious social problems in Karabakh.
In 1998, a decision was taken to resume the work of the Karabash medeplavile complex.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabakh plant - environmental.
By the early 2000s, Karabakh was already known as the zone of environmental disaster.
The situation on the Karabashmedi began to change in 2004, after the enterprise went under the control of the Russian copper company.
The company began to carry out a modernization of production, which began to gradually reduce the environmental burden on the environment.
This was recently noted by the Governor of Chelyabinsk region Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in the first few of July.
The head of the South Urals has called the grand changes that have taken place with the enterprise since Karabashmed moved into the RMK group.
The main event for the modernization of Karabashmedi in recent years was the construction of a new sulfuric acid store, which allows to capture up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the President of the Russian copper company Vsevolod Levin, the amount of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of JSC "Karabashmed" is the reconstruction of the conversion.
The replacement of three converters, incinerators, gas pipelines is planned for the end of 2017.
The cost of the project is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016 it is planned to launch a new workshop for cleaning industrial goods worth 1 billion rubles.
In turn, the amounts of taxes charged to the budget of the city of Karabash will increase.
For the entire period of implementation of the Tominsky GOK project - from the beginning of construction and until the introduction into operation of the second line - the federal penalty will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the introduction of the GOK into operation, the income of taxes in the budgets of all levels can be 80.9 billion rubles.
During the year of production in the Varna region, 346.3 million rubles were listed in budgets of different levels.
And this is for the first year.
“The longer the company works successfully, the higher the amount of deductions can be,” Valery Ulanovsky added.
In the RMK, it was clarified that in 2015 the tax deductions from the Mikhailovsky GOK approximated 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of the enterprises of the RMK in the life and development of the territories of their presence is not limited to tax deductions.
The enterprises of the RMK help to repair and contain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, improve the territory.
In 2016, one of the largest social projects of the Russian copper company in Karabakh became a major renovation, and in fact - almost complete reconstruction of the kindergarten N9 per 95 pupils.
The building, built in 1960, was in a state of emergency.
Also on the territory of "RMK Arena" will be located a landscape park with artificial pond, underground and underground parking for 600 cars, cafes and sports shops.
"RMK Arena" will allow to conduct spectacular professional sports events of the international level.
