FAS fined Google nearly half a billion rubles
The reason was a violation of competition in the mobile application market.
The anti-monopoly trial was started on the initiative of Yandex.
The Russian company claimed that Google provides smartphone manufacturers with access to Android components under conditions that have banned pre-installation of apps from other developers, in particular from Yandex.
The FAS found confirmation of these claims and found that the company abused the dominant position in the market and forced mobile device manufacturers to install along with the Google Play store other apps.
According to the results of the inspection, the Federal Antimonopoly Service decided to punish Google, said the deputy head of the FAS Alexey Dotsenko.
The fine must be paid within 60 days after the entry into force of the decree.
The FAS concluded that the law on protection of competition should be respected by all companies, including transnational corporations.
In turn, Google intends to study the solution first and only then will determine with further actions: to execute it or to challenge it.
The Federal Anti-Monopoly Service recognized the company as a breach of the competition law as early as September last year and ordered the contracts to be adjusted until December 18.
However, Google did not agree to this.
Since then, the company and the department have been conducting legal proceedings.
The FAS noted that despite the fine, they are discussing with Google the possibility of concluding a world agreement.
This measure will not lead to anything.
Such an opinion was expressed by the leading analyst of Mobile research group Eldar Murtazin.
Murtazin also noted that the fine will not affect either the users or the competitiveness of the corporation.
