The new data helps astronomers understand why the stars in the cluster rotate at different speeds, as well as how periods of rotation relate to the formation of planets.
“We hope that by comparing our results with other stellar clusters, we will learn more about the relationship between the star’s mass, its age and even the history of its solar system,” said study co-author Luisa Riball, a researcher and researcher in the study.
